      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SNEAKY PHILTRA (5) was in the money at this track two runs ago before having her colours lowered at her latest appearance over 2190m here, beaten 21 metres. Ideally placed and is sure to prove tough to beat. ROCKING WROXTON (9) settled handy but couldn't finish the race off and could only manage seventh last start over 1790m at this circuit, that effort coming after a minor placing at this venue the run before. Hard to know where he gets from this slightly awkward draw. This looks a sterner test than last time but on his best form he is capable of a far better performance. CHALKNCHEDDAR (6) was responsible for a better effort last time out when third over 1700m at Horsham. Should run a big race. HESASTAR (8) is worth some thought after his last-start fifth over 2190m at this course on June 26. One for the exotics players.",
